foia:ProcessedRequestSection.foia:FootnoteText: FAA - The number of requests pending as of the start of the FY is 22 lower than reported in last year's annual report as pending at the end of FY 2009. The adjustment primarily reflects requests where final action was taken by all appropriate FAA offices in FY 2009, but not all database closures were entered into the database until FY 2010. (Note: FOIA requests assigned to multiple FAA offices are not considered closed until the last FAA office responds to the requester.)

FHWA - The number of requests pending as of the start of the FY is 2 lower than reported in last year's annual report as pending at the end of FY 2009. The adjustment reflects cases that were closed in FY 2009, but not closed out in the database until FY 2010.

MARAD - The number of requests pending as of the start of the FY is 3 lower than reported in last year's annual report as pending at the end of FY 2009. The adjustment reflects cases that were closed in FY 2009, but not closed out in the database until FY 2010.
Agency Overall - For the reasons stated above, the number of requests pending as of the start of the FY is 27 lower than reported in last year's annual report as pending at the end of FY 2009.
